-- EU Could Give Spain Another Year to Meet Deficit Goal, Pais Says
-- B y   M a n u e l   B a i g o r r i
-- 2012-05-30T06:15:39Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-30/eu-could-give-spain-another-year-to-meet-deficit-goal-pais-says.html
The European Commission plans to ask
European Union finance ministers for their approval for  Spain  to
have one more year to meet the budget deficit target of 3% of
gross domestic product, El Pais reported. * Deficit goal of 3%
would be delayed to 2014 instead of 2013, the newspaper said *
Commission also asks for measures including an increase of VAT,
El Pais reports * El Pais cites a draft of recommendations by
the commission to be presented today * Link to website:
www.elpais.com  To contact the reporter on this story:
